Package fr.lirmm.chocominer.api.services.managers

Class AbstractDeclarativeManager

java.lang.Object
fr.lirmm.chocominer.api.services.managers.AbstractDeclarativeManager
Direct Known Subclasses:
ARMDeclarativeManager, IMDeclarativeManager
public class AbstractDeclarativeManager extends Object
An abstraction for declarative data mining managers. Contains generic methods and information tha all declarative managers have in common.

    • getConstraints

      public List<ConstraintInterface> getConstraints(ConstraintsRequest constraintsRequest) throws InvocationTargetException, InstantiationException, IllegalAccessException, UndefinedConstraintParameterException, NotEnoughParametersException
      Creates a list of concrete ConstraintInterface instances based on the provided ConstraintsRequest, using the ParameterBuilder which extracts the method arguments to create a concrete constraint and finds the corresponding ConstraintParameter contained in a given APIConstraint.
      Parameters:
      constraintsRequest - The request containing a list of APIConstraint instances.
      Returns:
      A list of instantiated concrete ConstraintInterface objects.
      Throws:
      InvocationTargetException - If an error occurs while invoking the constructor of the concrete constraint.
      InstantiationException - If an error occurs while instantiating the concrete constraint.
      IllegalAccessException - If an error occurs due to illegal access while creating the concrete constraint.
      UndefinedConstraintParameterException - If a constraint parameter is undefined or missing.
      NotEnoughParametersException - If there are not enough arguments to instantiate the concrete constraint.
